oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Everbright mansion
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Exterior view of the Everbright mansion. People and horse-drawn carriages are outside the building. The home served as a residence to the Bennett family, and also was a temporary school building for Battle Ground Academy in the early 1900s.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Houses; Carriages & coaches; Horses
